===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*kʷer-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Breteyn}}, from {{inh|en|ang|Breoton}}, {{m|ang|Bryten}} etc., from {{der|en|la|Britannia}}; later reinforced by {{der|en|xno|Britaine}}, {{der|en|fro|Bretaigne}}, from {{der|en|la|Brittannia}}, variant of {{m|la|Britannia}}, from {{m|la|Britannī}}. Ultimately from {{der|en|cel-bry-pro|*Prɨdėn|t=Britain}} from ''*Pritanī'' (also compare {{m|cel-bry-pro|*Prɨdɨn|t=Picts}} from ''*Pritenī''), attested to in Ancient Greek as {{l|grc|Πρεττανική}}, compare {{cog|cy|Prydain}}. {{doublet|en|Brittany}}. More at {{l|la|Britto}}.

